entries.femaleVariant: Tell me about Randy. What kinda kid he is.
Petty theft, drugs, runnin' away from home – that kind.
OK, lemme hear it…
Tell me more about Randy?
Haven't mentioned Randy's dad.
Where's Randy's dad?
Cop uncles really see the best in ya…
There're people who always find their way into trouble. Randy's one of 'em.
Been a few years since he got popped. Gang war.
It's just, uh... It's not easy for me to talk about what's bitin' at my ass.
Not worried Yawen's gonna toe the line, rat you out to her superiors?
Think Yawen'll actually help us, all things considered?
entries.maleVariant: Ya think Yawen'll actually help us, all things considered?

entries.femaleVariant: Sign me up. We find Randy, then we find the bottoms of a few bottles.
Really oughta focus on finding Randy now.
Let's focus on finding Randy.
Sign me up for that beer.
Shouldn't we be looking for Harris's place?
Huh, great role model.
Gonna tell me why we aren't we tryna find Harris's apartment?
An' besides, we are trying. Wanna see if we can find some connection to Harris at Randy's.
Pretty weak lead.
Best we can hope for just now.
Booted off the force…
Didn't tell me you got fired.
Lost your badge, didn't tell me about it – why?
So, got booted off the force…
Ugh, suspended. Mayor's death stank to high heaven. Inquest into – kicked under the rug. So I made a fuss.
Not worth askin' how you feel about that.
Nope.
I… don't know.
Makes you a bit of a leadhead, doe'n't it?
entries.maleVariant: Makes you a bit of a leadhead, don't it?

entries.femaleVariant: Used to be friends. Doubt she'd do that.
Yeah. These tiffs of ours always end up the same way.
I'll tell ya about it over a beer sometime.
'Course.
It'll be my pleasure.
Joss was left alone with three. Hm... But she's as tough as weathered leather.
Think Yawen'll help?
Yawen not gonna report you?
It's a house. And I doubt he's keepin' his victims in his basement.
That it do.
Plus, not that I'd use it... but I do know one skeleton she'd prefer remain tucked in her closet.
All right, this is it.
Fair enough. Could tell me where we're headed, though.
To Joss's.
Randy's mom.
She thinks he just ran away from home. For now, keep the kidnapping between us.
